race.comment: IRREVERENT (11) should take beating. She resumed over 1300m at Sandown Hillside and ran a strong race in a good maiden, finding the line well to be beaten 0.7 lengths in third. She'll improve off that and gets every chance on speed from the inside gate. THE BENCHMARK (9) has placed in both starts to date, close up in one of these maidens on debut, good again at Sandown Hillside when in the market. He can continue to improve and take beating here. PERFECT LINK (7) is a gelding by Brazen Beau on debut for the Eurell yard who are going well. He's jumped out and trialled well and has claims. LUXOR GOLD (4) is a gelding by Pariah on debut for the Eurell yard who can also run well.
